parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or hesitate, increasing the risk of a crash, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power while driving
hesitates
stalls
or fails to accelerate; the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears; the vehicle makes a whining
grinding
or screeching sound; the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission pump can cause the transmission to lose hydraulic pressure, leading to a loss of motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The transmission pump fails
causing a loss of hydraulic pressure; the vehicle loses power while driving; the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears; the vehicle makes a whining or grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip or hesitate, leading to a loss of motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The torque converter fails
causing the transmission to slip or hesitate; the vehicle loses power while driving; the transmission makes a grinding or whining sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Active Head Restraint (AHR) can cause the headrest to deploy unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or distractions while driving.
symptoms: The headrest deploys suddenly
without warning
and without the vehicle being involved in a crash. The plastic clips or retainers that hold the metal bar in place break
causing the headrest to deploy. The failure can occur while the vehicle is in motion or stationary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door lock actuator can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave passengers stranded.
symptoms: The door makes a loud buzzing or clicking noise when locking or unlocking
the door will not unlock or lock
the door is stuck in the locked or unlocked position
the door opens or closes on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to loss of power and braking, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
loss of power and braking
the engine and electrical functions remain in operation after the ignition is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning and Heating System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning and heating system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning or heating only works on one side of the vehicle
hot air blows out of the vents
strong fumes emit inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and stalls
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine leaks oil
the engine light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of various systems can cause discomfort, distraction, or safety hazards while driving.
symptoms: The blind spot module smokes due to water damage
the passenger side airbag explodes
the headlights dim or brighten randomly
the vehicle's GPS system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door actuator can cause the door to become stuck in a locked position, making it difficult or impossible for passengers to exit the vehicle in an emergency, which can lead to serious safety risks.
symptoms: The sliding door will not open or unlock
making a buzzing sound when attempting to unlock
and may get stuck in a locked position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the vehicle to become unbearably hot, leading to discomfort and potential health risks, especially in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The air conditioning system blows hot air
only blows cold air on the driver's side
or makes a loud noise when turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden deployment of the headrest can cause injury or distraction to the driver or passenger, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The headrest deploys suddenly without a collision
hitting the driver or passenger in the back of the head.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leak of the oil filter housing can cause the engine to seize up, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil filter housing
pooling in the engine crevice
and may not provide a warning before the engine seizes up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
causing the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC system can cause the vehicle to become unbearably hot or cold, leading to discomfort and potential health risks.
symptoms: The HVAC system does not work properly
blowing hot or cold air
or making a loud noise when turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw of the armrest console can cause personal items to become lost or hidden, leading to potential conflicts or distractions while driving.
symptoms: Personal items become lost or hidden in the armrest console
causing conflicts or distractions while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to retrieve recall information using the VIN can cause owners to be unaware of potential safety risks or necessary repairs.
symptoms: The VIN does not yield any results when entered into the NHTSA website
making it difficult to determine if the vehicle is subject to any recalls.
